TITLE: Exposing Worker Functionality in threads.js (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to expose functionality from a worker thread using threads.js. The `expose` function from the `threads/worker` module is used to define a function (`hashPassword`) that can be called from the main thread. The worker thread calculates a SHA256 hash of the provided password and salt and returns the result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/andywer/threads.js/blob/master/docs/getting-started.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// workers/auth.js - will be run in worker thread
import sha256 from "js-sha256"
import { expose } from "threads/worker"

expose({
  hashPassword(password, salt) {
    return sha256(password + salt)
  }
})
```

