TITLE: Spawning a simple worker - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the basic usage of `spawn()` to create a worker thread, call a function within it, and terminate the thread. It imports `spawn`, `Thread`, and `Worker` from the threads.js library and defines an asynchronous `main` function to handle worker interaction. The worker executes a simple addition function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/andywer/threads.js/blob/master/docs/usage.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// master.js
import { spawn, Thread, Worker } from "threads"

async function main() {
  const add = await spawn(new Worker("./workers/add"))
  const sum = await add(2, 3)

  console.log(`2 + 3 = ${sum}`)

  await Thread.terminate(add)
}

main().catch(console.error)
```

