TITLE: Scheduling Tasks with pool.queue() in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the function signature for scheduling tasks using `pool.queue()`. The `TaskFunction` type defines the function that will be executed by a worker, and the `pool.queue()` method returns a promise that resolves when the task is completed or rejects if the task fails.
SOURCE: https://github.com/andywer/threads.js/blob/master/docs/usage-pool.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
let pool: Pool<ThreadType>
type TaskFunction<ThreadType, T> = (thread: ThreadType) => Promise<T> | T

pool.queue<T>(task: TaskFunction<ThreadType, T>): Promise<T>
```

