TITLE: Master Thread: Streaming Results from Worker
DESCRIPTION: This master thread code spawns a worker, subscribes to the `values` observable, and calls the `add` method on the worker with several values. Finally, it calls the `finish` method and terminates the worker.
SOURCE: https://github.com/andywer/threads.js/blob/master/docs/usage-observables.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// master.js
import { spawn, Thread, Worker } from "threads"

const minmax = await spawn(new Worker("./workers/minmax"))

minmax.values().subscribe(({ min, max }) => {
  console.log(`Min: ${min} | Max: ${max}`)
})

await minmax.add(2)
await minmax.add(3)
await minmax.add(4)
await minmax.add(1)
await minmax.add(5)
await minmax.finish()

await Thread.terminate(minmax)
```

