TITLE: Bundle Install and Jekyll Serve
DESCRIPTION: Installs the required gems using Bundler and then starts the Jekyll server to serve the documentation locally.  The `--path vendor/bundle` option installs gems into the vendor/bundle directory. The `--baseurl ''` option tells Jekyll to serve the site from the root directory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/andywer/threads.js/blob/master/docs/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
bundle install --path vendor/bundle
bundle exec jekyll serve --baseurl ''
```

