TITLE: Waiting for Tasks to Complete in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to wait for a subset of tasks to complete using `Promise.all()` and a list of `QueuedTask` objects.  Other pool tasks might still be running.
SOURCE: https://github.com/andywer/threads.js/blob/master/docs/usage-pool.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
// (Created a pool and queued other pool tasks beforeâ€¦)

const myTasks: QueuedTask[] = []

for (let input = 0; input < 5; input++) {
  const task = pool.queue(worker => worker.work(input))
  myTasks.push(task)
}

await Promise.all(myTasks)
console.log("All worker.work() tasks have completed. Other pool tasks might still be running.")
```

