TITLE: Pool Options Interface in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript interface defines the available options when creating a thread pool. It allows customization of concurrency, maximum queued jobs, pool name, and pool size, providing control over the pool's behavior and resource usage.
SOURCE: https://github.com/andywer/threads.js/blob/master/docs/usage-pool.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
interface PoolOptions {
  concurrency?: number
  maxQueuedJobs?: number
  name?: string
  size?: number
}
```

