TITLE: Cancelling a Queued Task in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to cancel a queued task using the `cancel()` method. Note that tasks can only be cancelled if they have not yet started executing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/andywer/threads.js/blob/master/docs/usage-pool.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const task = pool.queue(multiplierWorker => multiplierWorker(2, 3))
task.cancel()
```

